ğŸ“Œ Project Overview
This project presents a data-driven analysis of U.S. federal debt trends using Excel. Built under a simulated business case for a Washington, D.C. debt agency, the goal was to analyze and forecast Debt Held by the Public, Intragovernmental Holdings, and Total Public Debt Outstanding to support policy and financial decision-making.

It includes data cleaning, transformation, visualization, seasonal pattern analysis, and long-term forecasting, with insights relevant to both public policy and private sector planning.

