ğŸ’¡ Key Insights
Structural Risk: U.S. debt is now rising independently of crisis events, due to long-term structural spending and interest costs.

COVID Acceleration: Public debt increased over 25% in 2020 alone.

Seasonal Behavior: Borrowing typically peaks in Q4â€“Q1 and dips during tax season (April).

Forecast Warning: Without major policy shifts, projected growth suggests an unsustainable fiscal path by the end of the decade.

