ğŸ§¾ Summary Conclusion
This project blends data cleaning, economic analysis, visualization, and forecasting to uncover how U.S. public debt has evolved across decades. What began as reactive borrowing in crisis periods has become a structural norm, raising red flags for policymakers, markets, and the public.

For businesses, governments, and analysts, these insights support smarter budget planning, interest rate forecasting, and fiscal risk management. This project also demonstrates my ability to combine technical Excel skills with real-world business intelligence and strategic foresight.
